Project Summary
===============
NextJS 15 Starter Template ŌĆö a minimal, production-ready foundation for building modern web applications. Pre-configured with TypeScript, Tailwind CSS 4, and essential Next.js App Router patterns. Ships with a placeholder HomePage component ready to be replaced by the user's app.

Architecture Overview
====================
Single-page Next.js App Router app with Supabase persistence. Server Components by default; any interactivity lives in client components under `components/`. Top-level routing files (`page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `not-found.tsx`, `error.tsx`, `loading.tsx`) are all server components ŌĆö `'use client'` NEVER appears at this level (breaks WebContainer prerendering). Styling is Tailwind CSS 4 via `@import "tailwindcss";` in `app/globals.css`. Supabase client is initialised in `lib/supabase.ts`; types in `types/database.ts`.

Key Components
==============

- **Page** (`app/page.tsx`) ŌĆö Server Component wrapper. Imports and renders `<Counter />`. Must stay a Server Component.
- **Counter** (`components/Counter.tsx`) ŌĆö Client Component. Main teller UI with increment/decrement/reset. Loads initial count from Supabase on mount, inserts a log row on every action, shows last 5 actions in real time.
- **RootLayout** (`app/layout.tsx`) ŌĆö Root HTML shell. Loads Geist Sans + Geist Mono via `next/font/google` and defines SEO metadata. Antialiasing enabled.
- **Error Boundary** (`app/error.tsx`) ŌĆö Runtime error recovery with retry.
- **NotFound** (`app/not-found.tsx`) ŌĆö 404 page. Plain server component using only `Link` from `next/link` and inline SVG.
- **Loading** (`app/loading.tsx`) ŌĆö Route transition spinner.

Agent Memory
============
- `.walden-memories/` ŌĆö shared folder where specialists write working documents for each other. Design specs, debug reports, SEO audits. Agents read from here instead of receiving large specs through Walden's token budget.

Invariants
==========
- `app/*/page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `not-found.tsx`, `error.tsx` are ALWAYS Server Components. No `'use client'`, no hooks, no event handlers at this layer.
- Client interactivity (useState, useEffect, onClick) lives in `components/*.tsx` with `'use client'`.
- Supabase database with `counter_logs` table. Env vars: `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY`. RLS enabled with anon insert + select policies. No auth required.
- `.env.local` exists at project root but is managed by the app (not written by agents directly).

Notes for agents
================
- Dependencies, versions, and the directory tree are NOT duplicated here. Read `package.json` or `list_directory` for that.
- When you change the project structure, update THIS file accordingly: add new components under Key Components, document new invariants, update the Architecture Overview if the fundamental shape shifts.
